mod_cron is a task scheduler for zotonic framework.

mod_cron can launch any M:F(A) in very flexible time cycles.


== Quickstart ==

1. zotonic installmodule mod_cron
2. Go to /admin/modules
3. Activate cron
4. Press F5. "Cron" button on left bar should appear.
5. Click on it (or go to /admin/cron)
6. This is mod_cron entry point. Click on "add job" button.
7. In dialog appeared, you need to fill name of job, describe time intervals and
   M:F(A) to run.

